{"_response_info":{"status":"ok"},"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/asbo.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/asbo","title":"Getting an ASBO","format":"answer","details":{"need_id":"473","business_proposition":false,"alternative_title":"Getting an Anti-social Behaviour Order (ASBO)","overview":"Find out what happens if you are given an Anti-social Behaviour Order (ASBO).","body":"\n<div class=\"summary\">\n<p>Anyone over the age of 10 can get an Anti-social Behaviour Order (<abbr title=\"Anti-social Behaviour Order\">ASBO</abbr>)</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>You can get an <abbr title=\"Anti-social Behaviour Order\">ASBO</abbr> if you have behaved &lsquo;anti-socially&rsquo;. This includes:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>drunken or threatening behaviour</li>\n  <li>vandalism and graffiti</li>\n  <li>playing loud music at night</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Getting an <abbr title=\"Anti-social Behaviour Order\">ASBO</abbr> means you won&rsquo;t be allowed to do certain things, such as:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>going to a particular place, eg your local town centre</li>\n  <li>spending time with people who are known as trouble-makers</li>\n  <li>drinking in the street</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>If you get an <abbr title=\"Anti-social Behaviour Order\">ASBO</abbr> it will last for at least 2 years. It could be reviewed if your behaviour improves.</p>\n\n<p>If you donâ€™t obey the <abbr title=\"Anti-social Behaviour Order\">ASBO</abbr>, you could be taken to court.</p>\n\n"},"updated_at":"2012-10-13T19:27:06+00:00","tags":[{"title":"Courts, sentencing and tribunals","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/justice%2Fcourts-sentencing-tribunals.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Attending courts, paying fines, appealing a sentence and tribunals","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=justice%2Fcourts-sentencing-tribunals","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/justice/courts-sentencing-tribunals"},"parent":{"title":"Crime, justice and the law","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/